It's the final week of the regular season for high school football in mid-Michigan. At stake are conference titles, playoff berths, and perfect records. 
As usual, we'll keep you updated with all the latest scores, starting around 7 p.m. Contribute to our updates by tweeting to @LSJsports with the hashtag #mipreps . Looking for box scores? Friday's stats will be available late in the evening here . 
LSJ sports reporters James Edwards and Brian Calloway will be live tweeting tonight. Follow Calloway for updates on Grand Ledge vs. Holt in a battle for the CAAC Blue title. Edwards will be covering Marshall vs. Portland in a matchup where the Raiders hope to keep their perfect season intact.
